author: CNET
description:
iPhone. AIPhone. Robot Phone?!?

Announced alongside the launch Honor Magic8 series, the company just shared a teaser video of the 'Robot Phone' concept which integrates "AI intelligence, robotic functionality, and handheld imaging."

We don't know much about this phone but more details will be unveiled at Mobile World Congress in March 2026. 

Would this be a phone you'd want? #tech #concept #robotphone #honor #smartphone #robotics #honorphone
title: HONOR Teases A Robot Phone Concept That Has A Pop-Up Camera and Gimbal 📲🤖

author: CNET
description:
The new ROG Xbox Ally comes in two models: the $1,000 Ally X and the $600 Ally. The key differences between the two are in their processors, storage and memory.

The Xbox Ally will have the AMD Ryzen Z2 A Processor, while the Xbox Ally X will use the faster AMD Ryzen AI Z2 Extreme Processor. Memory will be different, with the lower-priced Xbox Ally having 16GB of LPDDR5X-6400 and the higher-cost handheld coming with 24GB of LPDDR5X-8000 RAM.

Both will come with solid-state storage, but the Xbox Ally will have 512GB, and the Xbox Ally X will have 1TB. Let's unbox the two new gaming handhelds. #asus #gaming #gaminghandheld #xboxally #asusrog #unboxing
title: Unboxing the $600 Asus ROG Xbox Ally and the $1,000 Asus ROG Xbox Ally X
